    title: "Liberian Dollar Ends March Near L$184 to the US Dollar, Up 8% on the Year",
    summary: "The Liberian dollar closed March 2026 at L$183.93 per US dollar — about 8% stronger than a year earlier, supported by booming gold exports and steady remittances, though it has given back ground since the end of 2025. In a dual-currency, import-dependent economy, the rate shapes everything from fuel prices to inflation.",
